cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the effects of RF impairments on spectrum sensing in cognitive radio systems, which involves signal processing, wireless communication, and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which covers topics related to signal processing and communication. The paper also discusses the impact of RF impairments on cooperative sensing in CR networks, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper considers the system-level effects of RF impairments, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper specifically focuses on cognitive radio systems, which can be classified under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
